# Bucket Sort

## Problem

Bucket Sort is a sorting algorithm that divides elements into different buckets, sorts each bucket separately, and then combines all buckets to get the final sorted array.

It works efficiently for uniformly distributed data.

---

# Algorithm / Pseudo Code

BEGIN

INPUT array A
INPUT n

CREATE n empty buckets

// Insert elements into buckets
FOR i = 0 TO n-1

    COMPUTE index = A[i] * n

    INSERT A[i] INTO bucket[index]

ENDFOR

// Sort each bucket
FOR i = 0 TO n-1

    SORT bucket[i]

ENDFOR

// Merge buckets
INITIALIZE k = 0

FOR i = 0 TO n-1

    FOR each element x IN bucket[i]

        A[k] = x

        k = k + 1

    ENDFOR

ENDFOR

PRINT sorted array

END
---

In Bucket Sort:

n = number of elements in the array
k = number of buckets

# Time Complexity

| Case       | Complexity |
| ---------- | ---------- |
| Best Case  | O(n + k)   |
| Worst Case | O(n²)      |

---

# Space Complexity

O(n + k)

---

# Important Points

* Distributes elements into buckets.
* Each bucket is sorted separately.
* Efficient for uniformly distributed data.
* Uses extra space.
* Mostly used for floating point numbers.
